title: For Sale:  Remington 700 Custom
postcontent: For sale is a Remington 700 in 300 winchester short mag. The receiver has been trued and lugs lapped to 85-90% contact and bolt fitted to the race by gunsmiths at Scheels in Des Moines IA, I have receipts to verify this. The bolt is a one piece bolt from Pacific Tool & Gauge with M16 extractor. The barrel is a Black Hole Weaponry chambered in 300 Winchester Short Mag with 3 land polygonal rifling, 1:8.5 twist rate. Muzzle threaded 5/8x24 with a surefire warcomp suppressor adapter currently mounted (has been mounted since the rubber thread protector was removed to protect the crown). The barrel has an M24 "heavy" profile and is made of shot peened stainless steel. The current round count on this barrel is 92. The proper break in procedure found in the Barnes reloading manual 4th edition was followed to ensure longer barrel life, greater accuracy, and ease of cleaning. This barrel has only been touched with a one piece carbon fiber .30 cal rod. This is a "rem/age" type barrel so the headspace is easily adjusted with a savage barrel nut wrench. The rifle currently will NOT chamber most factory loaded ammunition, it is set for my hand loads. If desired I will readjust the headspace to accept standard SAAMI loads prior to completing the sale. The action is sitting in a Bell & Carlson A2 stock. The stock has been bedded to this action using devcon epoxy and the barrel channel has been inletted to allow for free floating of the heavier profile barrel. The optic is a Sig Optics Tango-4 6-24x50 first focal plane scope with illuminated reticle. It is a mil scale reticle with mil adjustments. I would consider selling the rifle without the optic at a reduced price. I also have 92 pieces of fireformed brass and ~130 pieces of un-fireformed brass (all federal headstamp) and redding competition 3 die set that I can sell with the rifle if desired. Contact me and I can send a picture of 5 shot group fired at 104 yards using 220 gr smk's and reloder 19 powder and full length sized brass. Thank you for taking the time to read this, Please dont hesitate to contact me with any questions. 816-three seven seven-9513.
